# Project Standards

This project uses a **requirements-first, audit-first** agent workflow. Follow it before writing or changing code.

## Read First

1. **`AGENTS.md`** — project overview, technology constraints, directory layout, coding standards, test commands, and PR checklist.
2. **`docs/AGENT_WORKFLOW.md`** — how to navigate docs, start tickets, and close work with audit evidence.

## Source of Truth

| Document | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| `docs/requirements.md` | Understanding stakeholder requirements (REQ IDs) |
| `docs/audit.md` | Verifying acceptance before marking tickets done (AUD IDs) |
| `docs/PRD.md` | Product goals, priorities, and detailed requirements |
| `docs/SDS.md` | API contracts, architecture, and implementation detail |
| `docs/ticket-tracker.md` | Current sprint, ticket status, dependencies, traceability |

## Implementing a Ticket

- Use **`.agents/workflows/implement-ticket.md`** as the step-by-step playbook.
- Save handover artifacts to **`docs/pr-messages/`** using **`docs/pr-messages/pr-template.md`**.
- Update **`docs/ticket-tracker.md`** when starting (🟢) and finishing (✅) a ticket.

## Rules

- Do not mark work complete without verifying relevant **AUD-*** items in `docs/audit.md`.
- Do not edit `docs/requirements.md` or `docs/audit.md` without explicit approval — they are acceptance gates.
- Match existing code conventions; prefer extending current patterns over new abstractions.
- Optional project skills live in `.agents/skills/`; supplemental rules in `.agents/rules/`.
